titleInfo.title: USA v. Holmes
titleInfo.subTitle: JUDGMENT as to Michael Holmes (1), Defendant plead guilty to Counts I and III of the Indictment and is committed to the Bureau of Prisons for 60 months; 5 years supervised release with special conditions; $100 special assesment; Count II of the Indictment is dismissed on the motion of the United States as to this defendant only; final order of forfeiture filed on 7/24/07 as to Count III; the defendant shall surrender for service of sentence at the institution designated by the Bureau of Prisons before 2:00 p.m. on September 22, 2008; the defendant shall forfeit the defendant's interest in the following property to the United States: $1,383 and $7,000 in U.S. Currency as to defendant Michael Holmes. Ordered by Judge Laurie Smith Camp. (4 certified copies to USM)(CJP)
